OL,6,FSir Brian recommends a new Crown Court
OL,7,FBench Division, made up of two
OL,8,Fmagistrates and a judge, that would
OL,9,Fhave the power to deal with all either-
OL,10,Fway offences.
OL,12,FEither-way offences are criminal
OL,13,Foffences that can be seen in a
OL,14,Fmagistrates court or crown court,
OL,15,Fdepending on their severity.
OL,17,FOffences categorised as 'either-way'
OL,18,Finclude fraud, child abduction, sexual
OL,19,Fassault and violent disorder.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/11
